---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro'
---

<Base
  title="Bermuda Local Deals and Offers"
  description="Where the value actually is in Bermuda — Restaurant Week, the grocery game, transport passes, free beaches, and how to find partner deals in the Pilot.BM directory."
>
  <section class="hero" style="padding-block: var(--space-16);">
    <div class="hero__inner">
      <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <ol class="breadcrumb" style="justify-content: center; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6);">
          <li><a href="/Pilot.BM/" style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6);">Home</a></li>
          <li class="breadcrumb__sep" aria-hidden="true">›</li>
          <li><a href="/Pilot.BM/live" style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.6);">Living</a></li>
          <li class="breadcrumb__sep" aria-hidden="true">›</li>
          <li style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9);">Deals and Offers</li>
        </ol>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="hero-title">Bermuda Local Deals</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">
        Where the value actually is — for residents and their guests.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="container" style="padding-block: var(--space-12);">

    <!-- Honest intro -->
    <section style="max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto var(--space-12);">
      <h2 style="font-size: var(--text-2xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-4);">A frank introduction</h2>
      <p style="color: var(--color-ink); margin-bottom: var(--space-4); line-height: 1.75;">
        Bermuda is expensive. There is no version of this page that changes that. A weekly grocery
        run for two people costs what it would cost for four in most US or UK cities. A lunch in
        Hamilton that would be $18 elsewhere is $30. Electricity is among the highest per-unit
        costs in the Atlantic world.
      </p>
      <p style="color: var(--color-ink); margin-bottom: var(--space-4); line-height: 1.75;">
        What this page offers is not a way around that reality but an honest map of where the
        genuine value pockets are. Some of them are significant — Restaurant Week, the right
        transport pass, knowing which grocery store to use for which category. Some of them are
        free. None of them require pretending you live somewhere else.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Dining deals -->
    <section style="margin-bottom: var(--space-12);">
      <h2 style="font-size: var(--text-2xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">Dining deals</h2>
      <p style="color: var(--color-muted); font-size: var(--text-sm); margin-bottom: var(--space-6);">When and where to eat without paying full price</p>

      <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-6);">

        <!-- Restaurant Week -->
        <div style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: var(--space-6);">
          <div style="display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: var(--space-3); margin-bottom: var(--space-3);">
            <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-xl);">Bermuda Restaurant Week</h3>
            <span style="font-size: var(--text-xs); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--color-ocean);">November</span>
          </div>
          <p style="color: var(--color-ink); margin-bottom: var(--space-3); line-height: 1.75;">
            The single best recurring value in Bermuda dining. More than 50 restaurants participate
            with prix-fixe menus — typically two or three courses for $45–$55. At restaurants where
            a comparable meal normally runs $80–$100 per person, that is a real discount, not a
            marketing gesture.
          </p>
          <p style="color: var(--color-ink); margin-bottom: var(--space-3); line-height: 1.75;">
            The programme runs roughly two weeks in November, despite the name. The best seats at
            popular restaurants fill in the first few days of bookings opening — sometimes within
            hours. Monitor <a href="https://www.table.bm" rel="noopener" target="_blank" style="color: var(--color-ocean);">Table.bm</a>
            from October onwards; booking opens a week or two before the event begins.
          </p>
          <p style="color: var(--color-ink); line-height: 1.75;">
            Practical notes: some restaurants offer the prix-fixe menu alongside their regular menu;
            others switch over entirely. Ask when booking. The prix-fixe price typically excludes
            drinks — factor that in. Book three or four restaurants when bookings open rather than
            committing to one; you can cancel the others.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Table.bm year-round -->
        <div style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: var(--space-6);">
          <div style="display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: var(--space-3); margin-bottom: var(--space-3);">
            <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-xl);">Table.bm — year-round specials</h3>
            <span style="font-size: var(--text-xs); font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.08em; color: var(--color-ocean);">Ongoing</span>
          </div>
          <p style="color: var(--color-ink); margin-bottom: var(--space-3); line-height: 1.75;">
            Table.bm lists dining deals and specials outside of Restaurant Week — early bird menus,
            Tuesday night specials, fixed lunch deals. Several Hamilton restaurants run quieter-night
            promotions on Mondays and Tuesdays that are not widely advertised elsewhere. Worth
            checking before booking a mid-week dinner.
          </p>
          <a href="https://www.table.bm" rel="noopener" target="_blank"
             style="font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-ocean); font-weight: 600;">
            Browse Table.bm deals →
          </a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The grocery game -->
    <section style="margin-bottom: var(--space-12);">
      <h2 style="font-size: var(--text-2xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">The grocery game</h2>
      <p style="color: var(--color-muted); font-size: var(--text-sm); margin-bottom: var(--space-6);">Bermuda has multiple grocery chains and they are not equivalent</p>

      <div style="background-color: var(--color-sand); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: var(--space-8); margin-bottom: var(--space-6);">
        <dl style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-5);">
          <div>
            <dt style="font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: var(--space-1);">MarketPlace</dt>
            <dd style="color: var(--color-ink); line-height: 1.75; margin: 0;">
              The workhorse chain with multiple locations across the island. Largest selection
              for everyday shopping. Member card discounts apply on rotating weekly specials —
              always worth having the card active. The Friday specials circular is worth
              checking before you shop.
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt style="font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: var(--space-1);">Miles Market</dt>
            <dd style="color: var(--color-ink); line-height: 1.75; margin: 0;">
              Hamilton's premium grocer. Better for specific imports, specialist items, and a
              deli counter that is genuinely good. Do not use it as your primary grocery shop —
              you will spend noticeably more for standard items. Use it for what it does well.
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt style="font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: var(--space-1);">Arnold's</dt>
            <dd style="color: var(--color-ink); line-height: 1.75; margin: 0;">
              Convenience-oriented, decent for basics and top-ups between larger shops.
              Not the right place for a weekly shop on price grounds.
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt style="font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: var(--space-1);">Supermart</dt>
            <dd style="color: var(--color-ink); line-height: 1.75; margin: 0;">
              Worth checking for specific categories where it runs competitive pricing.
              Particularly useful for wine and spirits relative to alternatives.
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt style="font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: var(--space-1);">Price Smart (membership warehouse)</dt>
            <dd style="color: var(--color-ink); line-height: 1.75; margin: 0;">
              Annual membership required. Comparable to Costco: bulk formats, lower per-unit
              cost on the categories they carry. Worth it for households of two or more people.
              Good for paper goods, cleaning supplies, bottled water, and select dry goods.
              Not useful for fresh produce or anything time-sensitive.
            </dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </div>

      <div style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: var(--space-5);">
        <p style="font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">Shopping tips that actually move the needle:</p>
        <ul style="padding-left: var(--space-5); color: var(--color-ink); display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-2); font-size: var(--text-sm);">
          <li>Buy local produce wherever it appears — Bermudian-grown vegetables and herbs are cheaper than imported equivalents and markedly fresher. Look for the "local" label at MarketPlace.</li>
          <li>Avoid grocery shopping at resort hotels or marina convenience stores. The mark-up is significant, not a rounding error.</li>
          <li>Meat is expensive island-wide; this is not a chain-specific problem. If you have storage, buying in bulk from Price Smart when cuts are available reduces the per-meal cost substantially.</li>
          <li>The MarketPlace member card weekly specials rotate on Thursdays. Check before your main shop.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Transport deals -->
    <section style="margin-bottom: var(--space-12);">
      <h2 style="font-size: var(--text-2xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">Transport</h2>
      <p style="color: var(--color-muted); font-size: var(--text-sm); margin-bottom: var(--space-6);">The bus and ferry network is the best deal in Bermuda transport</p>

      <div style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: var(--space-6); margin-bottom: var(--space-4);">
        <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-3);">Bus and Ferry Weekly Pass — $62</h3>
        <p style="color: var(--color-ink); margin-bottom: var(--space-3); line-height: 1.75;">
          Unlimited travel on all bus zones and all ferry routes for seven days. This is the
          best deal for getting around the island if you are using public transport more than
          three or four times in a week. The ferry in particular — Hamilton to the Royal Naval
          Dockyard, Hamilton to St. George's — is a meaningfully better way to travel than
          the corresponding bus routes, and is included on the same pass.
        </p>
        <p style="color: var(--color-ink); line-height: 1.75;">
          Monthly passes for residents are available at a lower effective daily rate (approximately
          $62–$95 per month depending on zone coverage). Purchase from the Hamilton Bus Terminal
          or from authorised token sellers. Token books are also available and represent better
          value than paying per-journey in cash, which incurs a premium.
        </p>
      </div>

      <p style="color: var(--color-muted); font-size: var(--text-sm); font-style: italic;">
        Pass pricing is set by the Bermuda Public Transportation Board and may change. Verify
        current rates at the Hamilton Bus Terminal on Church Street.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Directory partner deals -->
    <section style="margin-bottom: var(--space-12);">
      <h2 style="font-size: var(--text-2xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">Pilot.BM partner deals</h2>
      <p style="color: var(--color-muted); font-size: var(--text-sm); margin-bottom: var(--space-6);">Exclusive offers from Featured and Anchor directory partners</p>

      <div style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: var(--space-8); text-align: center;">
        <p style="color: var(--color-ink); margin-bottom: var(--space-4); line-height: 1.75;">
          Pilot.BM Featured and Anchor directory partners can publish exclusive deals directly
          in this section. Browse the directory for businesses marked with the Partner badge.
        </p>

        <div style="background-color: var(--color-amber-muted); border: 1px solid var(--color-amber); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: var(--space-4); margin-bottom: var(--space-6); text-align: left;">
          <p style="font-size: var(--text-sm); color: #92400e; margin: 0;">
            <strong>Deals will populate here as directory partners are onboarded.</strong>
            This section is reserved for Featured and Anchor partners — businesses that have
            claimed their listing at the $50/month or $100/month tier. If you are a local
            business, see the note at the bottom of this page.
          </p>
        </div>

        <a href="/Pilot.BM/directory" class="btn btn-secondary">
          Browse the directory →
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Free things for residents and guests -->
    <section style="margin-bottom: var(--space-12);">
      <h2 style="font-size: var(--text-2xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">Free things worth knowing about</h2>
      <p style="color: var(--color-muted); font-size: var(--text-sm); margin-bottom: var(--space-6);">For residents and for guests you are showing around</p>

      <div class="card-grid card-grid-3">
        <div style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: var(--space-5);">
          <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-lg); margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">The beaches</h3>
          <p style="font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-ink); line-height: 1.7;">
            All of Bermuda's beaches are public. Horseshoe Bay, Elbow Beach, Warwick Long Bay,
            John Smith's Bay — no entry fee on any of them. The South Shore beaches are the
            equal of anywhere in the Atlantic. The fact that they are free is something guests
            reliably underestimate.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: var(--space-5);">
          <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-lg); margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">Admiralty House Park</h3>
          <p style="font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-ink); line-height: 1.7;">
            The cliff-jumping at Admiralty House in Pembroke is one of Bermuda's best-kept open
            secrets from visitors. Free, accessible, and on a summer afternoon a social experience
            in its own right. The park itself has walking trails down to the water.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: var(--space-5);">
          <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-lg); margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">Fort Hamilton</h3>
          <p style="font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-ink); line-height: 1.7;">
            Five minutes from Hamilton city centre. The moat trail, the views over the city, the
            underground tunnels — free to enter. The Sunday afternoon bagpipe performance
            (seasonal) is a genuinely odd and memorable experience. No admission fee.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: var(--space-5);">
          <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-lg); margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">Cooper's Island Nature Reserve</h3>
          <p style="font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-ink); line-height: 1.7;">
            St. David's Island. Former NASA tracking station and US naval facility, now one of
            the island's best nature reserves. Several beaches, walking trails, and
            extraordinary views to the Atlantic. Free entry; requires a short drive or the
            bus to St. David's.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: var(--space-5);">
          <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-lg); margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">The Railway Trail</h3>
          <p style="font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-ink); line-height: 1.7;">
            The former Bermuda Railway right-of-way, converted to a walking and cycling trail
            running most of the island's length. Views you won't find from the road. Free.
            Good sections near Devonshire and Southampton if you don't want to commit to
            the full length.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: var(--space-5);">
          <h3 style="font-size: var(--text-lg); margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">Christmas Boat Parade</h3>
          <p style="font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-ink); line-height: 1.7;">
            December, Hamilton Harbour. Boats decorated with lights parade through the harbour
            on a Friday evening. Free to watch from anywhere along Front Street or the
            harbour-side restaurants. One of the best free events on the annual calendar.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA for businesses -->
    <div style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg); padding: var(--space-8); text-align: center; background-color: var(--color-sand);">
      <p style="font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">Are you a local business?</p>
      <p style="color: var(--color-ink); font-size: var(--text-sm); margin-bottom: var(--space-5); max-width: 560px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; line-height: 1.75;">
        Anchor-tier directory partners can publish deals and promotions directly in this section,
        reaching Pilot.BM's resident and visitor audience. See our listing tiers to find out what
        each level includes.
      </p>
      <a href="/Pilot.BM/directory/claim" class="btn btn-primary">
        Claim your listing →
      </a>
    </div>

  </div>
</Base>
